.START 

Chrysler Corp. 's Jeep/Eagle division said it signed three licensing agreements for the distribution of Jeep-brand shoes and shirts in the U.S. and Canada.
Terms of the agreement weren't disclosed. 

The licensees are Modern Shirt International and Modern Shirt Industries Ltd. and KangaROOS U.S.A. Inc. Jeep officials said the shirt companies will produce and distribute a line of Jeep sportswear to be retailed through department stores, while KangaROOS will produce and distribute Jeep athletic and casual shoes that will be sold through independent shoe stores. 

The Highland Park, Mich., company said the three licensees will work under the direction of Murjani Merchandising Ltd., which holds the Jeep-brand master license. 

